---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

<Layout title="John Locke: Consciousness Continuity as Proto-Trajectory | Foundations | Identity Engineering">
	<main class="min-h-screen">
		<section class="border-b border-white/10 px-6 py-16">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Foundations • John Locke</div>
				<h1 class="mt-3 text-5xl font-bold tracking-tighter text-white">Consciousness Continuity as Proto-Trajectory</h1>
				<p class="mt-4 text-xl text-white/70">18 July 2026 field analysis — translated and extended for public reference</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="px-6 py-16">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/80 space-y-8">
				<div>
					<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Context</div>
					<p>Start of the systematic field analysis. First deep dive into established identity theories to strengthen isomorphy work and positioning.</p>
				</div>

				<div>
					<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">1. Locke’s Empiricism</div>
					<p>Locke is the classical British empiricist. In the <em>Essay Concerning Human Understanding</em> (1689) he argues against the rationalists (Descartes et al.) who postulated innate ideas.</p>
					<ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 pl-5 list-disc text-white/70">
						<li><strong>Tabula Rasa</strong>: The mind at birth is a blank slate. All ideas come from experience.</li>
						<li><strong>Two sources of all ideas</strong>: Sensation (external world) and Reflection (internal operations of the mind: thinking, doubting, willing, perceiving).</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="mt-4">Philosophy as “research in the mind”: conceptual analysis and thought experiments. The framework is related here — it performs conceptual modeling (geometric primitives, world-line, gradient) inspired by empirical physics, currently without its own laboratory validation.</p>
				</div>

				<div>
					<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">2. Theory of Personal Identity</div>
					<p>Locke sharply distinguishes between <strong>Man</strong> (biological organism, bodily continuity) and <strong>Person</strong> (thinking, intelligent being with reason and reflection that can consider itself as itself).</p>
					<p>Personal identity consists solely in the <strong>continuity of consciousness</strong> (sameness of consciousness) over time — primarily mediated by memory, the ability to extend consciousness backward to past actions and thoughts.</p>
					<p class="mt-4">The Prince and the Cobbler thought experiment: the soul/consciousness of a prince enters the body of a cobbler. The <em>Person</em> remains the prince, accountable for princely deeds, even though the <em>Man</em> is now the cobbler. Identity tracks consciousness, not substance (body or soul).</p>
					<p>Person is a <em>forensic term</em>: it concerns accountability, responsibility, reward and punishment.</p>
				</div>

				<div>
					<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">3. Relevance for Identity Engineering</div>
					<ul class="space-y-4">
						<li><strong>Sameness-as-Trajectory</strong>: Locke supplies the historical root. Identity is not static substance but continuity of consciousness across time — a proto-trajectory. The framework extends this with the <em>active</em> component (Vision Gradient as prospective opening of future degrees of freedom) and geometric dynamics (Stem as stable axis around which consciousness continuity rotates).</li>
						<li><strong>State Differential</strong>: Corresponds to the backward extension of consciousness (memory as coherence maintenance).</li>
						<li><strong>Identity Stem</strong>: The “inner core” from which conscious continuity derives its stability — in Locke implicitly the “same self” that reflects.</li>
						<li><strong>Forensic Dimension</strong>: Fits the Architect level and the Dual Mission (responsibility in substrate-free contexts).</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="mt-4"><strong>Differentiation</strong>: Locke is retrospective and passive (memory-based). Identity Engineering is prospective and active (Vision Gradient + conscious design of the geometry). Locke shows that identity is “designable” in the sense of accountability — the framework makes this design aspect explicit and physics-informed.</p>
					<p><strong>Empirie Gap</strong>: Locke’s theory is pure thought experiment (no laboratory data). This is precisely where the framework begins: moving from philosophical analysis to engineering-supported, potentially empirically testable practice (Questions as Probes, operationalization via psychological process models).</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-16 bg-white/[0.015]">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-lg text-white/70">
				<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Next Steps in Field Analysis</div>
				<p>Next thinker: Parfit (<em>Reasons and Persons</em>) — direct successor and critic of Locke in the psychological continuity debate. Or immediate expansion of the mapping table and integration into Core Concepts or new Foundations pages.</p>
				<p class="mt-6 text-sm text-white/50">Status: First materialization of the Locke deep-dive as anchor for isomorphy work. Strengthens Positioning &amp; Differentiation.</p>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
